  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nCRI CPU metrics are incorrect when using a large number of cores, due to a `uint64` overflow.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nCPU metrics should be correct for arbitrarily high numbers of cores.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nDeploy a pod with 20 CPU units allocated, and fetch the CRI metrics. The metrics will be incorrect.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.14.4\r\n- CRI: CRI-O\r\n\r\ncc @paulnivin\r\ncc @ashleykasim\r\n/sig node\r\n/sig scalability",
